# Feature Comparison Matrix Template

**Note**: This is a template guide for creating Excel feature comparison matrices. Create actual .xlsx file using Python openpyxl or similar following xlsx skill patterns.

## Sheet 1: Feature Comparison

### Column Structure

| Column | Header | Purpose |
|--------|--------|---------|
| A | Feature Category | Group features (Core, Advanced, Integrations, etc.) |
| B | Feature Name | Specific feature |
| C | Our Product | ✅ / ❌ / ⚠️ / Rating 1-5 |
| D | Competitor 1 | ✅ / ❌ / ⚠️ / Rating 1-5 |
| E | Competitor 2 | ✅ / ❌ / ⚠️ / Rating 1-5 |
| F | Competitor 3 | ✅ / ❌ / ⚠️ / Rating 1-5 |
| G | Gap Analysis | We lead / Parity / We're behind / Missing |
| H | Priority | P0 / P1 / P2 / P3 |
| I | Notes | Additional context |

### Feature Categories

- Core Features
- Advanced Features
- Integrations
- Security & Compliance
- Performance & Scalability
- Support & Services
- Pricing Tiers
- Platform & Infrastructure

### Color Coding (Conditional Formatting)

- **Green** (We lead): Our rating > all competitors
- **Yellow** (Parity): Similar to competitors
- **Red** (We're behind): Competitors ahead of us
- **Gray** (N/A): Not applicable

